Gaming company Lotto Kenya, via the Lotto Foundation, has entered into a partnership with a number of Kenyan artistes ahead of it's mega jackpot draw.A lucky winner will pocket some Sh100 million after the draw is conducted on December 31, 2016.Leading to the draw, the company signed an agreement with rappers Frasha and Femi One, gospel acts Kele Takatifu and DJ Sadic to synthesize the youth on responsible gaming.The Foundation will then join hands with the artistes in their various charity causes, as a way of giving back to the community.